{"tid":1166830,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"黃台仰：諗起香港會喊","createTime":"2019-05-22T16:30:03.000Z","updateTime":"2019-05-23T02:03:05.000Z","uid":97961,"like":27,"dislike":9,"uniUserReply":15,"replies":[{"pid":"8c491c18ff311cb47bf4a1514ba0a6da430daa08","tid":1166830,"uid":97961,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-05-22T16:30:03.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.ft.com/content/edd3b148-7c32-11e9-81d2-f785092ab560\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Fedd3b148-7c32-11e9-81d2-f785092ab560&d=cCjVArjaL4JVgeQxTlbTS%2BBrFmK%2FfjgW9YhWFGnkYF4%3D&h=7f20aa76\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.ft.com/content/edd3b148-7c32-11e9-81d2-f785092ab560</a><br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;No one likes to leave the place where you grow up, it is a big price for me to pay,&rdquo; said one of the activists, Ray Wong Toi-yeung, in an exclusive interview with the FT. <span style=\"color: gold;\">He said he wept one day while on the street in Germany because he missed his own culture and home so much.</span><br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;I will never be able to come back if Hong Kong can extradite me back to China once I return,&rdquo; he said. &ldquo;It is important for me to speak up as one of the first political refugees of Hong Kong.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"/assets/faces/fs/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"12bb3a90542dbe71942cbdb262632642a35f7bb3","tid":1166830,"uid":13663,"like":4,"dislike":3,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-05-22T16:30:50.000Z","msg":"好好生活"},{"pid":"76045ffc1dd765e4aa1fdfb301e5149eb7e8b37b","tid":1166830,"uid":37363,"like":30,"dislike":2,"score":28,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-05-22T16:45:37.000Z","msg":"佢可能成世返唔到屋企<img src=\"/assets/faces/fs/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n同時，所有香港人都每分每秒失去緊屋企<img src=\"/assets/faces/fs/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n重喺香港，可以企出嚟嘅，6月9號見<img src=\"/assets/faces/fs/hoho.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"d64fde7812856baad4fc0b78b0f173a3e69c9bcd","tid":116